  <section id="Palace">
    <h2>Palace</h2>
    <article>
      <h3>Taj Mahal:Symbol of love</h3>
      <img src="https://qph.cf2.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-6813eff3fd95a77be237c791498a1265-lq">
      <p>The Taj Mahal, located in Agra, India, is one of the most iconic structures in the world. It is a stunning monument to love and a masterpiece of Mughal architecture. I recently had the opportunity to visit this wonder of the world and was blown away by its grandeur and beauty.
As I approached the Taj Mahal, I couldn't help but feel overwhelmed by its sheer size and intricate details. The white marble structure is breathtaking, with its domed central building flanked by four minarets on each corner. The intricate carvings and inlay work on the walls and floors are truly awe-inspiring.
As I stepped inside, I was struck by the quiet serenity that enveloped me. The marble floors were cool and smooth beneath my feet, and the sunlight filtering through the windows created a soft, ethereal glow. The central chamber houses the tombs of Emperor Shah Jahan and his beloved wife, Mumtaz Mahal, for whom the Taj Mahal was built.
The story of the Taj Mahal is a testament to the enduring power of love. Emperor Shah Jahan commissioned the construction of the Taj Mahal in memory of his wife, who died giving birth to their 14th child. The Taj Mahal took 22 years to build, with thousands of workers laboring day and night to create this masterpiece.
I spent several hours exploring the various chambers and gardens surrounding the Taj Mahal. The intricate waterworks and fountains in the gardens were particularly impressive, and I spent some time sitting by the reflecting pool, taking in the beauty of the Taj Mahal from a distance.

Overall, my visit to the Taj Mahal was a truly unforgettable experience. The grandeur and beauty of this iconic structure are simply breathtaking, and it's easy to see why it's considered one of the wonders of the world. If you ever get the chance to visit Agra, I highly recommend taking the time to explore the magnificence of the Taj Mahal.</p>



      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taj_Mahal">Read More</a>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Maysor Palace:A Spectacular Example of Indian Royalty</h3>
      <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/7b/04/23/7b0423384aac539cfca2fabebd2c2618.jpg">
      <p>The palace has several rooms, including the Kalyana Mantapa or the marriage hall, the Durbar Hall, and the Ambavilasa or the public hall. The walls of the palace are decorated with beautiful paintings, and the floors are made of Italian marble.
One of the most striking features of the palace is the illuminated facade. Every Sunday and on special occasions, the palace is illuminated with thousands of bulbs, creating a stunning sight that attracts crowds from far and wide.
Visiting Mysore Palace
Mysore Palace is open to visitors from 10:00 am to 5:30 pm every day, except on Sundays and public holidays when it is illuminated. Visitors can explore the palace and its grounds, and guided tours are also available. The palace also hosts cultural events and exhibitions, providing visitors with an insight into the rich cultural heritage of the city.

Mysore Palace is a must-visit destination for anyone interested in the history and culture of India. Its magnificent architecture, opulent interiors, and rich history make it a fascinating place to visit. If you're planning a trip to India, don't miss the chance to visit Mysore Palace and witness the grandeur of Indian royalty</p>
