  <section id="Temple">
    <h2>Temple</h2>
    <article>
      <h3>Tirupati Balaji</h3>
      <img src="https://www.aartigyan.com/Images/TampleImages/1536754468toll.jpg">
      <p>Tirupati Balaji, also known as Lord Venkateswara, is a highly revered deity in Hinduism. The temple of Tirupati Balaji, located in the town of Tirumala in Andhra Pradesh, India, is considered one of the most visited and wealthiest temples in the world.
The temple is situated on the top of a hill, which requires devotees to climb over 2,000 steps to reach the shrine. The journey can be challenging, but the breathtaking view and spiritual atmosphere make it a unique and unforgettable experience.
Tirupati Balaji is believed to be the lord of wealth, and his blessings are sought after by many devotees. The temple has various rituals and offerings that are made to Lord Venkateswara, including the famous 'Tirupati Laddu,' which is considered a sacred offering.
Every year, millions of devotees visit the temple to seek the blessings of Tirupati Balaji, and the temple has a unique system of managing the crowds to ensure that everyone has a chance to see the deity and offer their prayers.

Visiting Tirupati Balaji is not just a religious pilgrimage but also a cultural experience that offers a glimpse into the rich history and traditions of India.</p>
