  <section id="Hill-Station">
    <h2>Hill Station</h2>
    <article>
      <h3>Gulmarg:A Snowy Paradise in the Heart of Kashmir</h3>
      <img src="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/50450082.cms">
      <p>Nestled in the heart of Kashmir, Gulmarg is a small town that transforms into a winter wonderland during the colder months. This picturesque town is known for its snow-covered peaks, dense forests, and pristine lakes. Gulmarg is a popular destination for skiing, snowboarding, and other winter sports.
The town is surrounded by the majestic Himalayan range, providing breathtaking views at every turn. The main attraction of Gulmarg is the Gulmarg Gondola, the highest cable car in the world. The Gondola takes visitors to an altitude of 4,100 meters, providing panoramic views of the valley below.
In addition to winter sports, Gulmarg also offers hiking and trekking opportunities during the warmer months. The Alpather Lake is a popular trekking destination, surrounded by snow-capped peaks and alpine meadows.
For those interested in history and culture, Gulmarg is also home to several ancient shrines and temples. The Shrine of Baba Reshi, located in the nearby village of Ziarat, is a revered pilgrimage site for both Hindus and Muslims.
Gulmarg is also known for its warm hospitality and delicious local cuisine. The town has a variety of restaurants and cafes that serve traditional Kashmiri dishes, such as Rogan Josh and Dum Aloo.

Whether you are a winter sports enthusiast, a nature lover, or a history buff, Gulmarg has something for everyone. So pack your bags and head to this snowy paradise in the heart of Kashmir for a once-in-a-lifetime experience</p>
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gulmarg">Read More</a>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Munnar:A Paradise on Earth</h3>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Munnar_hillstation_kerala.jpg/1200px-Munnar_hillstation_kerala.jpg">
      <p>Munnar is a picturesque hill station located in the Indian state of Kerala. Situated at an altitude of 1,600 meters above sea level, it is known for its breathtaking scenery, lush greenery, and tea plantations. Munnar is a popular tourist destination that attracts visitors from all over the world.

The weather in Munnar is pleasant throughout the year, making it a perfect getaway destination. The monsoon season in Munnar is from June to September, and the winter season is from November to February. The temperature during the winter season can drop down to 5 degrees Celsius, making it a perfect place for people who love to experience the chilly weather.
Munnar is known for its tea plantations, and a visit to Munnar is incomplete without visiting the tea gardens. The tea gardens in Munnar are spread across acres of land, and the views are breathtaking. Visitors can take a walk through the tea plantations, watch the tea processing, and even taste some freshly brewed tea.
Apart from the tea plantations, Munnar has several other attractions such as the Eravikulam National Park, Mattupetty Dam, Echo Point, and Top Station. The Eravikulam National Park is home to the endangered Nilgiri Tahr and is a must-visit for nature lovers. Mattupetty Dam is a popular picnic spot and is known for its beautiful landscapes. Echo Point is a place where visitors can shout and hear their voices echo back. Top Station is the highest point in Munnar and offers a panoramic view of the Western Ghats.
Munnar is also known for its adventure activities such as trekking, rock climbing, and paragliding. The lush green hills, tea plantations, and scenic landscapes make it an ideal place for adventure enthusiasts.

In conclusion, Munnar is a paradise on earth and a must-visit destination for nature lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and anyone who wants to experience the beauty of nature. The serene surroundings, pleasant weather, and breathtaking views make Munnar an unforgettable experience.</p>
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Munnar">Read More</a>
    </article>
